# Microfinance Loan Portfolio — SQL Project

Domain:** Financial Services | Microfinance
Tool:**  MySQL
Dataset:** 300 rows · 15 columns · Synthetic data

## What This Project Is About

A microfinance institution (MFI) gives small loans — between ₹5,000 and ₹30,000 — to low-income borrowers like street vendors, farmers, weavers, and auto-rickshaw drivers across 8 Indian states. These borrowers usually don't have access to regular banks, so the MFI is their only source of credit.

The credit and operations team needs answers from their loan data every day — who is paying late, which officers are doing well, which states are risky, and how much interest the institution will earn. This project answers all of that using SQL.

## Files in This Project

| File | What it contains |
|---|---|
| `mfi_loan_data.csv` | The dataset — 300 loan records |
| `mfi_project_v2.sql` | All SQL code — schema, exploration, and 15 business questions |
| `README_v2.md` | This file |

## The Dataset

**Table name:** `mfi_loans`

| Column | Type | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `loan_id` | TEXT | Unique loan ID (e.g. LN-0001) |
| `borrower_id` | TEXT | Unique borrower ID (e.g. BRW-0001) |
| `state` | TEXT | Indian state where the borrower lives |
| `occupation` | TEXT | What the borrower does for a living |
| `loan_amount` | REAL | Amount of money given out, in ₹ (INR) |
| `interest_rate_pct` | REAL | Annual interest rate charged (18%–26%) |
| `tenure_months` | INTEGER | How long the borrower has to repay (6–24 months) |
| `disbursement_date` | DATE | The date the loan was handed out |
| `repayment_frequency` | TEXT | How often the borrower pays — Weekly, Bi-Weekly, or Monthly |
| `loan_purpose` | TEXT | Why the borrower needed the money |
| `loan_officer_id` | TEXT | The field officer assigned to this loan |
| `emi_amount` | REAL | The fixed monthly repayment amount in ₹ |
| `days_past_due` | INTEGER | How many days the borrower is late (0 = paying on time) |
| `loan_status` | TEXT | Current state — Active, Closed, or NPA |
| `credit_score` | INTEGER | Internal score from 300 (poor) to 850 (excellent) |

**A note on loan_status:**
- **Active** — loan is ongoing and borrower is still repaying
- **Closed** — loan has been fully repaid
- **NPA** — Non-Performing Asset; borrower has stopped paying (defaulted)

## How to Run This Project

### MySQL
```sql
LOAD DATA INFILE 'mfi_loan_data.csv'
INTO TABLE mfi_loans
FIELDS TERMINATED BY ','
IGNORE 1 ROWS;
-- Replace STRFTIME('%Y', ...) with YEAR(disbursement_date)
```

## SQL Concepts Covered

| Concept | Where it appears |
|---|---|
| `SELECT`, `FROM`, `WHERE` | BQ-11, BQ-12, BQ-13 |
| `GROUP BY`, `ORDER BY` | BQ-01 through BQ-10 |
| `COUNT`, `SUM`, `AVG`, `MIN`, `MAX` | BQ-01 through BQ-14 |
| `LIMIT` | BQ-06, BQ-07, BQ-13 |
| `CASE WHEN` | BQ-05, BQ-07 |
| `DISTINCT` | Data Exploration |
| Date functions (`STRFTIME`) | BQ-09 |
| `ROUND` | Throughout |
| Window function — `RANK() OVER` | BQ-15 |

